Step 1: Install Samba

On Rocky Linux:

sudo dnf install samba samba-client -y

Verify installation:

rpm -qa | grep samba

Expected output:

samba
samba-client
samba-common
Step 2: Start Samba Service
sudo systemctl enable smb --now
sudo systemctl enable nmb --now

Check status:

sudo systemctl status smb

You should see:

Active: active (running)
Step 3: Create Department Folder

Suppose HR department needs shared storage.

sudo mkdir /hr-data

Set permissions:

sudo chmod 770 /hr-data
Step 4: Create User

Create an HR user:

sudo useradd hruser
sudo passwd hruser

Example:

New password:
Retype new password:
Step 5: Add Samba Password

Linux password and Samba password are separate.

sudo smbpasswd -a hruser

Example:

New SMB password:
Retype new SMB password:
Added user hruser
Step 6: Configure Samba Share

Open configuration:

sudo vi /etc/samba/smb.conf

Add:

[HR]
path = /hr-data
browseable = yes
writable = yes
valid users = hruser
read only = no
Step 7: Verify Configuration
testparm

Expected:

Loaded services file OK.

No errors should appear.

Step 8: Restart Service
sudo systemctl restart smb
Step 9: Configure Firewall
sudo firewall-cmd --permanent --add-service=samba
sudo firewall-cmd --reload

Verify:

sudo firewall-cmd --list-services
Step 10: Check Server IP
ip a

Example:

192.168.1.100
Step 11: Access from Windows

Press:

Windows + R

Enter:

\\192.168.1.100\HR

Windows asks:

Username: hruser
Password: ********

After login, users can upload and download files.
